# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: HassarPath | Scene: HassarPath3
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Sarah woke to the rise of natural light."
    new "Sarah woke to the rise of natural light."

    old "The intricate construction of the sanctum made it hard to trace where anything ever really came from."
    new "The intricate construction of the sanctum made it hard to trace where anything ever really came from."

    old "Trapped in the center of the palace, it was like a maze within a maze."
    new "Trapped in the center of the palace, it was like a maze within a maze."

    old "Still, Sarah was glad that there was at least a natural rhythm to the day. Something ordinary in this otherwise odd place."
    new "Still, Sarah was glad that there was at least a natural rhythm to the day. Something ordinary in this otherwise odd place."

    old "She stretched her arms out."
    new "She stretched her arms out."

    old "A relaxing pain ran through her arms, the kind that did not stress her, but rather only reminded her of the extends of her body."
    new "A relaxing pain ran through her arms, the kind that did not stress her, but rather only reminded her of the extends of her body."

    old "Part of her hated herself for having slept so well, knowing that in this very city, many of her countrymen likely did not enjoy the luxuries she did."
    new "Part of her hated herself for having slept so well, knowing that in this very city, many of her countrymen likely did not enjoy the luxuries she did."

    old "But then again, neither had they enjoyed her luxuries in Rosanna either."
    new "But then again, neither had they enjoyed her luxuries in Rosanna either."

    old "Sarah sighed. Even in defeat, she bore the advantages of her birth."
    new "Sarah sighed. Even in defeat, she bore the advantages of her birth."

    old "As she climbed out of her bed, she gazed across the room."
    new "As she climbed out of her bed, she gazed across the room."

    old "The splendor of it still seemed so excessive as to border on absurd."
    new "The splendor of it still seemed so excessive as to border on absurd."

    old "The more she studied it, the more she noticed that there were objects that seemed clearly different from the others."
    new "The more she studied it, the more she noticed that there were objects that seemed clearly different from the others."

    old "Loot, she realized."
    new "Loot, she realized."

    old "The tribesmen had a trivial economy of their own, rather, they relied on raiding the neighbouring regions for their wealth."
    new "The tribesmen had a trivial economy of their own, rather, they relied on raiding the neighbouring regions for their wealth."

    old "Judging by the room, it had worked well for them."
    new "Judging by the room, it had worked well for them."

    old "Sarah walked through the door, leaving her room behind."
    new "Sarah walked through the door, leaving her room behind."

    old "As she moved through the twisting hallways of the sanctum, Sarah found herself naturally drawn back to the bathhouse, where she had first entered."
    new "As she moved through the twisting hallways of the sanctum, Sarah found herself naturally drawn back to the bathhouse, where she had first entered."

    old "The soft mist that moved across the surface of the water, hinted at its heat."
    new "The soft mist that moved across the surface of the water, hinted at its heat."

    old "It felt instantly relaxing to her skin."
    new "It felt instantly relaxing to her skin."

    old "Closing her eyes, Sarah took a deep breath, the scented air filling her nostrils."
    new "Closing her eyes, Sarah took a deep breath, the scented air filling her nostrils."

    old "For a moment, she was at peace."
    new "For a moment, she was at peace."

    old "Suddenly, Sarah opened her eyes again in response to the sound of something moving in the water."
    new "Suddenly, Sarah opened her eyes again in response to the sound of something moving in the water."

    old "She saw Naydeen, swimming towards her."
    new "She saw Naydeen, swimming towards her."

    old "Hi Sarah, I hope you had a good night sleep."
    new "Hi Sarah, I hope you had a good night sleep."

    old "Sarah smiled and nodded at Naydeen."
    new "Sarah smiled and nodded at Naydeen."

    old "Yes, I slept surprisingly well, actually."
    new "Yes, I slept surprisingly well, actually."

    old "I bet you did."
    new "I bet you did."

    old "Sarah saw Naydeen wink at her. She didn't know what to make of it. Had Hassar spoken to her of what had transpired between them?"
    new "Sarah saw Naydeen wink at her. She didn't know what to make of it. Had Hassar spoken to her of what had transpired between them?"

    old "The bed was incredibly soft, and the room...it's beautiful."
    new "The bed was incredibly soft, and the room...it's beautiful."

    old "I told you, we are well provided for."
    new "I told you, we are well provided for."

    old "She motioned towards Sarah."
    new "She motioned towards Sarah."

    old "Come, join me."
    new "Come, join me."

    old "For a moment she was hesitant, but Sarah couldn't deny that she wanted to feel the water on her skin."
    new "For a moment she was hesitant, but Sarah couldn't deny that she wanted to feel the water on her skin."

    old "Slowly walking into the pool, Sarah could feel the warm water rise up along her body."
    new "Slowly walking into the pool, Sarah could feel the warm water rise up along her body."

    old "As it neared her hips, Sarah could feel whatever tension that was left in her body, fade away into nothingness."
    new "As it neared her hips, Sarah could feel whatever tension that was left in her body, fade away into nothingness."

    old "Whatever soothing properties the mist in the room had, the water held it in tenfold."
    new "Whatever soothing properties the mist in the room had, the water held it in tenfold."

    old "This water is incredible."
    new "This water is incredible."

    old "It flows here from a nearby desert oasis. The irrigation project was quite a challenge, all things considered."
    new "It flows here from a nearby desert oasis. The irrigation project was quite a challenge, all things considered."

    old "But the water is said to contain unique properties by the tribes."
    new "But the water is said to contain unique properties by the tribes."

    old "Sarah began to slowly swim, drawing nearer to Naydeen."
    new "Sarah began to slowly swim, drawing nearer to Naydeen."

    old "You know a lot about the tribesmen, don't you?"
    new "You know a lot about the tribesmen, don't you?"

    old "Naydeen smiled as she swam close to Sarah."
    new "Naydeen smiled as she swam close to Sarah."

    old "I should, I am one of them."
    new "I should, I am one of them."

    old "Sarah couldn't say she was entirely surprised. The complexion of her skin had hinted as much."
    new "Sarah couldn't say she was entirely surprised. The complexion of her skin had hinted as much."

    old "Does that surprise you?"
    new "Does that surprise you?"

    old "Not entirely, only, I thought only slaves were kept here."
    new "Not entirely, only, I thought only slaves were kept here."

    old "Naydeen shook her head."
    new "Naydeen shook her head."

    old "I am no slave. Quite the opposite."
    new "I am no slave. Quite the opposite."

    old "Her face grew serious."
    new "Her face grew serious."

    old "I am the Khan's wife."
    new "I am the Khan's wife."

    old "Sarah was stunned. She had imagined Naydeen was here on account of the same reasons as her. A conquered people."
    new "Sarah was stunned. She had imagined Naydeen was here on account of the same reasons as her. A conquered people."

    old "But instead, she was his wife."
    new "But instead, she was his wife."

    old "That's...he keeps his wife locked up here?"
    new "That's...he keeps his wife locked up here?"

    old "Again, with the language, sweet child. Locked up? Do I look like I am in prison?"
    new "Again, with the language, sweet child. Locked up? Do I look like I am in prison?"

    old "Sarah watched Naydeen swim, her beautiful body only visible through the prism of the water's surface."
    new "Sarah watched Naydeen swim, her beautiful body only visible through the prism of the water's surface."

    old "She didn't appear a slave, nor in any worry."
    new "She didn't appear a slave, nor in any worry."

    old "No...I guess you don't."
    new "No...I guess you don't."

    old "The Khan has many wives, as is his right by virtue of his status and our society, but I was his first."
    new "The Khan has many wives, as is his right by virtue of his status and our society, but I was his first."

    old "Sarah could see Naydeen smiled and drew some pride from that fact."
    new "Sarah could see Naydeen smiled and drew some pride from that fact."

    old "So why are you here then?"
    new "So why are you here then?"

    old "Because in all the city there is no better place to be."
    new "Because in all the city there is no better place to be."

    old "And should I want to leave, I need only ask my husband, and I will be provided with an escort to leave."
    new "And should I want to leave, I need only ask my husband, and I will be provided with an escort to leave."

    old "Sarah watched as Naydeen swam closer. Her voice softened."
    new "Sarah watched as Naydeen swam closer. Her voice softened."

    old "But you'll find, should you leave, that the city of Al'Gahaem is a nasty place."
    new "But you'll find, should you leave, that the city of Al'Gahaem is a nasty place."

    old "Noise. Filth. Constant buzzing."
    new "Noise. Filth. Constant buzzing."

    old "It is all the things this place is not. So I much rather remain here."
    new "It is all the things this place is not. So I much rather remain here."

    old "Sarah watched the incredible bathhouse, the paradise that had been built in the heart of the palace, just for her and the others."
    new "Sarah watched the incredible bathhouse, the paradise that had been built in the heart of the palace, just for her and the others."

    old "But even if it's nice, isn't this still a prison of sorts?"
    new "But even if it's nice, isn't this still a prison of sorts?"

    old "Have you ever heard of a prison you can leave whenever you want?"
    new "Have you ever heard of a prison you can leave whenever you want?"

    old "Sarah considered. She had to admit she never had. She shook her head."
    new "Sarah considered. She had to admit she never had. She shook her head."

    old "But, is this all you can do? Just swim and...exist?"
    new "But, is this all you can do? Just swim and...exist?"

    old "The compound is large."
    new "The compound is large."

    old "There is the bathhouse, yes, but there are also the private quarters."
    new "There is the bathhouse, yes, but there are also the private quarters."

    old "Then there are the gardens. The library. The dressing hall. The viewing tower."
    new "Then there are the gardens. The library. The dressing hall. The viewing tower."

    old "Really, if there is even a thing you might miss, ask and Hassar will provide it."
    new "Really, if there is even a thing you might miss, ask and Hassar will provide it."

    old "Sarah and Naydeen swam towards the edge of the pool, resting against the side of it."
    new "Sarah and Naydeen swam towards the edge of the pool, resting against the side of it."

    old "But I suspect I don't need to tell you about the gardens."
    new "But I suspect I don't need to tell you about the gardens."

    old "Naydeen winked again."
    new "Naydeen winked again."

    old "I...what are you implying?"
    new "I...what are you implying?"

    old "Naydeen reached out and brushed Sarah's hair from her face."
    new "Naydeen reached out and brushed Sarah's hair from her face."

    old "Don't worry. The Khan holds no secrets from us. He told me about your evening in the garden."
    new "Don't worry. The Khan holds no secrets from us. He told me about your evening in the garden."

    old "To have debased herself like that was one thing. To now have other people know about it, somehow worse."
    new "To have debased herself like that was one thing. To now have other people know about it, somehow worse."

    old "I didn't, it just-"
    new "I didn't, it just-"

    old "Naydeen shushed her to be still."
    new "Naydeen shushed her to be still."

    old "It's ok, Sarah. I'm happy for you."
    new "It's ok, Sarah. I'm happy for you."

    old "Sarah looked at her, confused."
    new "Sarah looked at her, confused."

    old "Yes, I had hoped you would come to see that Khan Hassar is a worthy man. One worth your affections."
    new "Yes, I had hoped you would come to see that Khan Hassar is a worthy man. One worth your affections."

    old "I don't love him if that's what you're saying."
    new "I don't love him if that's what you're saying."

    old "Of course not. Such things do not happen overnight. But I pray you will come to see what me and the others see in him."
    new "Of course not. Such things do not happen overnight. But I pray you will come to see what me and the others see in him."

    old "For you to have showed your respect for him like that, and so soon, it makes me happy."
    new "For you to have showed your respect for him like that, and so soon, it makes me happy."

    old "Sarah, not knowing what to say, opted to say nothing."
    new "Sarah, not knowing what to say, opted to say nothing."

    old "The two women suddenly looked to the side as a new figure emerged."
    new "The two women suddenly looked to the side as a new figure emerged."

    old "A woman walked up towards the edge of the pool and slowly entered."
    new "A woman walked up towards the edge of the pool and slowly entered."

    old "For a moment, Sarah struggled to understand her proportions."
    new "For a moment, Sarah struggled to understand her proportions."

    old "Thin of face, and thin of frame, the woman struck her as almost frail...except for her belly."
    new "Thin of face, and thin of frame, the woman struck her as almost frail...except for her belly."

    old "Large and bloated, protruding far ahead of her."
    new "Large and bloated, protruding far ahead of her."

    old "Only after a moment did Sarah understand."
    new "Only after a moment did Sarah understand."

    old "Pregnant."
    new "Pregnant."

    old "The woman was with child."
    new "The woman was with child."

    old "Once submerged in the water, the woman casually swam up to the both of them."
    new "Once submerged in the water, the woman casually swam up to the both of them."

    old "A new friend, have we?"
    new "A new friend, have we?"

    old "Naydeen smiled at the woman."
    new "Naydeen smiled at the woman."

    old "Ayaka, meet Sarah. Sarah, meet Ayaka."
    new "Ayaka, meet Sarah. Sarah, meet Ayaka."

    old "The woman extended her hand and Sarah took it."
    new "The woman extended her hand and Sarah took it."

    old "Ayaka, but you can just call me Aya, everbody does really."
    new "Ayaka, but you can just call me Aya, everbody does really."

    old "Nice to meet you."
    new "Nice to meet you."

    old "It seemed so odd to Sarah, to be exchanging pleasantries with these women as thought this was all completely normal."
    new "It seemed so odd to Sarah, to be exchanging pleasantries with these women as thought this was all completely normal."

    old "Did you manage to sleep well, Aya?"
    new "Did you manage to sleep well, Aya?"

    old "Ayaka nodded."
    new "Ayaka nodded."

    old "As well as could be hoped. Sleeping sideways really helps a lot. I feel like he's kicking a lot less."
    new "As well as could be hoped. Sleeping sideways really helps a lot. I feel like he's kicking a lot less."

    old "Sarah watched as the woman traced the outline of her swollen belly with her hands, lovingly and gentle."
    new "Sarah watched as the woman traced the outline of her swollen belly with her hands, lovingly and gentle."

    old "The way a mother would."
    new "The way a mother would."

    old "You're pregnant..."
    new "You're pregnant..."

    old "Sarah saw Aya smile at her."
    new "Sarah saw Aya smile at her."

    old "How astute of you."
    new "How astute of you."

    old "But yes, I am. Nearing on eight months. We should be close."
    new "But yes, I am. Nearing on eight months. We should be close."

    old "Sarah could see Aya smile at the idea."
    new "Sarah could see Aya smile at the idea."

    old "You've been here for that long?"
    new "You've been here for that long?"

    old "Aya shook her head."
    new "Aya shook her head."

    old "No, quite a lot longer. Perhaps, closer to two years?"
    new "No, quite a lot longer. Perhaps, closer to two years?"

    old "Sarah could see Aya looking at Naydeen for confirmation."
    new "Sarah could see Aya looking at Naydeen for confirmation."

    old "About two years, almost, I think."
    new "About two years, almost, I think."

    old "Aya laughed."
    new "Aya laughed."

    old "Time can be a bit weird here. You'd best figure out a way to keep track or you're going to lose it entirely."
    new "Time can be a bit weird here. You'd best figure out a way to keep track or you're going to lose it entirely."

    old "Aya placed her hands on her belly again, looking down at it with awe at her own miracle."
    new "Aya placed her hands on her belly again, looking down at it with awe at her own miracle."

    old "I was a noble lady from a small house on a border province in the far-east."
    new "I was a noble lady from a small house on a border province in the far-east."

    old "When the tribesmen came, they captured me and brought me here. I've been here ever since."
    new "When the tribesmen came, they captured me and brought me here. I've been here ever since."

    old "A story not unfamiliar to Sarah."
    new "A story not unfamiliar to Sarah."

    old "The same happened to me. Did you lose a lot of people close to you?"
    new "The same happened to me. Did you lose a lot of people close to you?"

    old "Aya suddenly laughed, catching Sarah by surprise."
    new "Aya suddenly laughed, catching Sarah by surprise."

    old "Ooh no, not a single one."
    new "Ooh no, not a single one."

    old "My brothers and my father mounted for war when the hordes came."
    new "My brothers and my father mounted for war when the hordes came."

    old "Then, when the first frontier unit was wiped out, they suddenly claimed they needed to perform a tactical retreat beyond the mountain pass."
    new "Then, when the first frontier unit was wiped out, they suddenly claimed they needed to perform a tactical retreat beyond the mountain pass."

    old "The whole house was packed up and we fled away beyond the mountains."
    new "The whole house was packed up and we fled away beyond the mountains."

    old "Aya paused for a moment."
    new "Aya paused for a moment."

    old "Or at least, we were supposed to."
    new "Or at least, we were supposed to."

    old "My brothers and father went to lead the head of the caravan, and my sisters and myself were near the back."
    new "My brothers and father went to lead the head of the caravan, and my sisters and myself were near the back."

    old "When the Khan's horde descended on our caravan, we were not even halfway there yet."
    new "When the Khan's horde descended on our caravan, we were not even halfway there yet."

    old "My brothers never so much as drew their swords."
    new "My brothers never so much as drew their swords."

    old "Aya laughed again."
    new "Aya laughed again."

    old "All my life they told me, a woman's duty is this, a man's duty is such."
    new "All my life they told me, a woman's duty is this, a man's duty is such."

    old "Aya impersonated their voices as she told the story."
    new "Aya impersonated their voices as she told the story."

    old "And all my life I was the perfect lady, performing my every duty just as was expected of me."
    new "And all my life I was the perfect lady, performing my every duty just as was expected of me."

    old "But where were they when it mattered? Where were they to discharge their manly duty?"
    new "But where were they when it mattered? Where were they to discharge their manly duty?"

    old "Aya spat in the water."
    new "Aya spat in the water."

    old "Cowards the lot of them."
    new "Cowards the lot of them."

    old "Sarah could see the anger in Aya's face and wasn't sure if it was her place to say anything."
    new "Sarah could see the anger in Aya's face and wasn't sure if it was her place to say anything."

    old "Anyway, ever since I've been here."
    new "Anyway, ever since I've been here."

    old "And your child...it's..."
    new "And your child...it's..."

    old "Aya nodded."
    new "Aya nodded."

    old "When I first came here, I rejected Hassar."
    new "When I first came here, I rejected Hassar."

    old "I think I even spat in his face."
    new "I think I even spat in his face."

    old "But when I learned of the betrayal of my family, how they had disgraced me, I began to hate them."
    new "But when I learned of the betrayal of my family, how they had disgraced me, I began to hate them."

    old "I cried and raged and cried again, but no matter what, Hassar remained."
    new "I cried and raged and cried again, but no matter what, Hassar remained."

    old "He listened. Let me cry. Let me rage. But he always listened."
    new "He listened. Let me cry. Let me rage. But he always listened."

    old "When it mattered...he was here for me."
    new "When it mattered...he was here for me."

    old "Aya sighed."
    new "Aya sighed."

    old "After that, I still rejected him, but my rejections grew softer and softer."
    new "After that, I still rejected him, but my rejections grew softer and softer."

    old "Eventually, with some liquid courage, I finally decided to give in to him."
    new "Eventually, with some liquid courage, I finally decided to give in to him."

    old "After that night, I couldn't imagine why I ever rejected him at all."
    new "After that night, I couldn't imagine why I ever rejected him at all."

    old "Pride? Loyalty? It all seemed so meaningless compared to just...being happy."
    new "Pride? Loyalty? It all seemed so meaningless compared to just...being happy."

    old "Aya breathed in deep and breathed out again, as if letting go of the stress."
    new "Aya breathed in deep and breathed out again, as if letting go of the stress."

    old "Then, a few months later, this happened."
    new "Then, a few months later, this happened."

    old "Sarah watched as Aya rubbed her own belly, a huge smile on her face."
    new "Sarah watched as Aya rubbed her own belly, a huge smile on her face."

    old "I was so scared to tell him, when I first realized. Scared he would be angry with him."
    new "I was so scared to tell him, when I first realized. Scared he would be angry with him."

    old "But it was the opposite."
    new "But it was the opposite."

    old "I think I never saw him as happy as I did when I finally told him."
    new "I think I never saw him as happy as I did when I finally told him."

    old "Listening to the story, Sarah continued to be confused by the man that had conquered her people."
    new "Listening to the story, Sarah continued to be confused by the man that had conquered her people."

    old "How could a man be capable of such kindness and such brutality, all at the same time."
    new "How could a man be capable of such kindness and such brutality, all at the same time."

    old "And yet, looking at Aya, Sarah saw nothing but love in her face for the man that had made her a slave."
    new "And yet, looking at Aya, Sarah saw nothing but love in her face for the man that had made her a slave."

    old "Would she ever be so foolish? Sarah couldn't imagine it."
    new "Would she ever be so foolish? Sarah couldn't imagine it."

    old "Then again, she could not have imagined doing what she had done in the garden, and still she had."
    new "Then again, she could not have imagined doing what she had done in the garden, and still she had."

    old "Anyway, I need to get some excercise in, the doctor told me it was good for the baby."
    new "Anyway, I need to get some excercise in, the doctor told me it was good for the baby."

    old "It was nice to meet you Sarah, I'm sure we'll speak again."
    new "It was nice to meet you Sarah, I'm sure we'll speak again."

    old "Sarah watched as Aya pushed herself off the side of the pool, swimming away as fast as her body allowed."
    new "Sarah watched as Aya pushed herself off the side of the pool, swimming away as fast as her body allowed."

    old "Sarah followed her with her eyes for a moment, trying to make sense of all she'd heard."
    new "Sarah followed her with her eyes for a moment, trying to make sense of all she'd heard."

    old "Ayaka is a nice girl."
    new "Ayaka is a nice girl."

    old "She took some time to get used to this place, but I think she's never been happier since."
    new "She took some time to get used to this place, but I think she's never been happier since."

    old "She does seem happy."
    new "She does seem happy."

    old "How does she know the child will be a boy?"
    new "How does she know the child will be a boy?"

    old "She has no idea, but she knows the Khan favors sons and so she simply hopes that by pretending, the world will follow."
    new "She has no idea, but she knows the Khan favors sons and so she simply hopes that by pretending, the world will follow."

    old "It could be a daughter just as easy."
    new "It could be a daughter just as easy."

    old "Sarah nodded, understanding."
    new "Sarah nodded, understanding."

    old "Have you given any consideration to what I told you?"
    new "Have you given any consideration to what I told you?"

    old "Sarah tried to recall."
    new "Sarah tried to recall."

    old "Consideration of what?"
    new "Consideration of what?"

    old "Serving the Khan does not come easy to most women, and he has his particularities."
    new "Serving the Khan does not come easy to most women, and he has his particularities."

    old "His tastes."
    new "His tastes."

    old "If you want, I can teach you. Show you how to please a man."
    new "If you want, I can teach you. Show you how to please a man."

    old "Sarah felt herself grow red in the face."
    new "Sarah felt herself grow red in the face."

    old "Agree, let Naydeen teach you"
    new "Agree, let Naydeen teach you"

    old "Despite her embrasement, Sarah gave her a quick nod."
    new "Despite her embrasement, Sarah gave her a quick nod."

    old "Naydeen gave her a soft smile."
    new "Naydeen gave her a soft smile."

    old "Don't worry, I will be gentle."
    new "Don't worry, I will be gentle."

    old "But for now, let's relax. We can continue this matter tonight."
    new "But for now, let's relax. We can continue this matter tonight."

    old "Sarah watched as Naydeen began to swam, and she found herself following her."
    new "Sarah watched as Naydeen began to swam, and she found herself following her."

    old "Refuse"
    new "Refuse"

    old "Sarah gave her a quick shake of the head."
    new "Sarah gave her a quick shake of the head."

    old "Naydeen smiled at her."
    new "Naydeen smiled at her."

    old "Very well. Perhaps it is better for you to find your own way to it."
    new "Very well. Perhaps it is better for you to find your own way to it."

    old "Sarah watched as Naydeen began to swim. Sarah remained, watching her from a distance."
    new "Sarah watched as Naydeen began to swim. Sarah remained, watching her from a distance."

    old "For a while longer, Sarah remained in the pool, trapped by its alluring properties."
    new "For a while longer, Sarah remained in the pool, trapped by its alluring properties."

    old "Time had a ways of slipping away from her in this place."
    new "Time had a ways of slipping away from her in this place."

    old "Before she knew it, the day had passed and she returned to her room, eager to sleep."
    new "Before she knew it, the day had passed and she returned to her room, eager to sleep."

    old "She felt her heart ache with guilt for her relaxation."
    new "She felt her heart ache with guilt for her relaxation."

    old "Walking through her room, Sarah casually ran her fingers past some of the objects."
    new "Walking through her room, Sarah casually ran her fingers past some of the objects."

    old "Solid, weighty, each had an air of quality about them."
    new "Solid, weighty, each had an air of quality about them."

    old "Catching herself, Sarah scolded herself for becoming too familiar with the place."
    new "Catching herself, Sarah scolded herself for becoming too familiar with the place."

    old "She had to keep herself from thinking of this as her room, rather than her prison, lest she forget what it was."
    new "She had to keep herself from thinking of this as her room, rather than her prison, lest she forget what it was."

    old "A sound near the door caused her to turn."
    new "A sound near the door caused her to turn."

